# Prettier ignore. Prettier runs from the repo root over JS/TS/JSON/YAML/MD/CSS;
# everything below is either not ours to format or regenerated by tooling, so
# formatting it just creates churn. Rust/Nix/TOML have no Prettier parser and are
# skipped automatically (treefmt → rustfmt / nixpkgs-fmt owns those).

# ─── Dependencies & build output ──────────────────────────────────────────
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/*.tsbuildinfo
/target/
/result

# ─── Nix / direnv caches ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
/.direnv/
/.devenv/

# ─── Lockfiles (machine-managed) ──────────────────────────────────────────
**/package-lock.json
**/pnpm-lock.yaml
**/yarn.lock
/Cargo.lock
/flake.lock

# ─── Generated by the flake on dev-shell entry — do NOT reformat ───────────
# README.md is assembled by v_flakes readme-fw from docs/.readme_assets/*;
# the rest are copied from the nix store / generated by the github module.
# Prettier would fight the generators and the diff would reappear next entry.
/README.md
/LICENSE
/.github/
/.pre-commit-config.yaml
